        <![CDATA[
        <b>Air Mouse Controls</b><br/><br/>
        • <b>Move cursor</b>: Rotate phone around Z axis (horizontal) and X axis (vertical).<br/>
        • <b>Left click</b>: Quick rotation around Y axis (leftwards).<br/>
        • <b>Right click</b>: Tilt phone right (configurable in Settings).<br/>
        • <b>Double click</b>: Two quick Y‑axis rotations.<br/>
        • <b>Scroll up/down</b>: Fast linear movement along Y axis (up/down).<br/><br/>
        <b>Tips</b><br/>
        • Calibrate sensors before first use.<br/>
        • Keep phone parallel to table, screen perpendicular to keyboard.<br/>
        • Use sensitivity slider to adjust cursor speed.<br/>
        • You can scan a QR code from your PC to auto‑fill the IP address.
        ]]>
    </string><string name="calibration_guide_content">
        <![CDATA[
        <b>How to Calibrate Sensors</b><br/><br/>
        <b>1. Gyroscope Calibration</b><br/>
        Place phone on a flat, still surface. Tap "Calibrate" and wait 5 seconds.<br/><br/>
        <b>2. Magnetometer Calibration</b><br/>
        Move phone in a figure‑8 pattern for 15 seconds. This improves orientation stability.<br/><br/>
        <b>3. Accelerometer Calibration</b><br/>
        Keep phone still on a flat surface. The app will measure gravity vector.<br/><br/>
        <b>4. Completion</b><br/>
        After calibration, the app will show "Sensors Ready". You\'re good to go!
        ]]>
    </string><string name="sensor_info_content">
        <![CDATA[
        <b>Device Sensors Used</b><br/><br/>
        • <b>Gyroscope (3‑axis)</b>: Measures angular velocity (rad/s). Used for cursor movement and click detection.<br/>
        • <b>Accelerometer (3‑axis)</b>: Measures linear acceleration (m/s²). Used for scroll detection and gravity reference.<br/>
        • <b>Magnetometer (3‑axis)</b>: Measures magnetic field (µT). Used for drift correction (optional).<br/><br/>
        <b>Missing sensors?</b><br/>
        If any sensor is missing, the app will still work with reduced functionality (e.g., no magnetometer).<br/><br/>
        <b>Sensor fusion</b><br/>
        We use a Madgwick filter to combine gyroscope, accelerometer and magnetometer data for accurate orientation.
        ]]>
    </string><string name="connection_guide_content">
        <![CDATA[
        <b>How to Connect to PC</b><br/><br/>
        <b>1. On your PC</b><br/>
        - Download and run the Air Mouse server application (provided separately).<br/>
        - Note the PC\'s IP address (e.g., 192.168.1.100).<br/><br/>
        <b>2. On your phone</b><br/>
        - Connect to the same Wi‑Fi network.<br/>
        - Enter the PC\'s IP address in the text field, or tap the QR button to scan a QR code from the PC.<br/>
        - Tap "Start Air Mouse".<br/><br/>
        <b>Troubleshooting</b><br/>
        • Ensure no firewall is blocking port 8080.<br/>
        • Try pinging the PC from the phone.<br/>
        • Check that both devices are on the same subnet.<br/>
        • If using a VPN, disable it temporarily.
        ]]>
